//pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=projectorion>projectorion</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Nuclear Renaissance Man</span><br>  Posts: 2809<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(1/5/03 11:05:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10.topic>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://news.nationalgeographic.com/news/2001/05/images/021011_nuclear.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   What if America took on more than it could chew?</span><hr size=1> What if the US took on more of the World than it could handle and lost? If a sizable part of Asia and the Middle East joined together out of resentment at sanctions and attacks on their nations. If the balance of power was fine enough. If China, Russia and others were forced to choose between the US and their neighbours. If animosity toward the US continues to escalate and they become isolated. If WW3 became America versus the World and they lost. Who would fill the void?<br>
<br>
Assuming nukes are eventually used then all the major nations would get knocked back a century or two. Japan, England, US, China, Russia, France, Germany, Switzerland, Israel, Italy Canada and anybody with a nuclearised enemy would be barbecued. Smaller nations would act quickly to take advantage of the missing nuclear umbrella provided by the West and fill the power vacuum. Africa would become even more anarchic than it is already with machete armed mobs massacring towns including women and children. Mexico would likely invade california. Indonesia would attack Australia. Damaged nations would be savaged by opportunistic neighbours and taken over. The entire political map of the World would change and the US would not be a part of it. The US would probably be renamed New New Mexico. Australia is already on Indonesian maps as part of their territory so very little will have changed from Indonesia's perspective I suppose.<br>
<br>
  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zentrander>Zentrander</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>NEP Freighter Crewman</span><br>  Posts: 96<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(1/6/03 5:43:30 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: What if America took on more than it could chew?</span><hr size=1> America has a navy, and more nukes than all those countries combined.  It couldnt lose.  Theres no way to invade, and america could flatten russia with a couple of nukes.  china too for that matter. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=atomicconspiracy>Atomic Conspiracy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 116<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(1/6/03 8:41:26 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Enough horse manure</span><hr size=1> I wonder how much real resentment there is at our &quot;bullying&quot; of savage tyrants around the globe, and how much of it is just envy-driven verbal abuse and self-loathing ingratitude from people who have little else. America-Haters accused us of &quot;bombing Afghanistan&quot;, as though everyone there is part of some ideological monolith drunk with their frenzied devotion to the Taliban. This is unlikely in either law or historical experience, and is also contradicted by something else that is in short supply among Hate America cultists: plain facts. In this case, the relevant one is that Afghans literally danced in the streets when the Americans came, as their fellow &quot;victims&quot; had done in Panama, Kuwait, Grenada, South Korea and even the capital and birthplace of ingrate politics, France. I don't think this is real, I don't believe the people of the world really support the ruthless dictators. If they do, they can share their fate. Bring it on.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zentrander>Zentrander</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>NEP Freighter Crewman</span><br>  Posts: 101<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(1/6/03 2:17:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Enough horse manure</span><hr size=1> I also think moth of it is envy.  However, we have made mistakes, but anti-american, i hesitate to say morons, but i will anyway, point to the wrong ones.  We have supported brutal dictators, such as those in Egypt and Iran, but these are not the issues anti-americans look at.  They are too dumb to delve beneath the easy to pick at Afghanistan, South Korea, Vietnam, etc.  Anything America does can be retaliated against via the &quot;Evil Americans&quot; card.<br>
<br>
if france, germany, england, or any country could enjoy the economic success we have, they would gladly do it.  Where is the backlash against russia for chechnya?  there is none, because nobody is jealous of russia.  anybody who is in power is envied and has enemies that try to topple them.  somalia was a humanitarian mission that just went awry. we shouldnt help people.  we are damned either way, so why risk american lives? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nuclaeon>Nuclaeon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Space Cadet</span><br>  Posts: 38<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(1/6/03 8:11:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Enough horse manure</span><hr size=1> I think a good way is to make a world dependent upon American generosity and fearful of American might.  I do think a new Marshall Plan could really do a lot.  It would create new resources and perhaps allow more people around the world to become educated so as to solve problems, not a bad thing in my estimation.  <br>
<br>
If they grow to envy us, so what?  It will only push them to work harder.  Not like they could do anything more than a dent of damage anyway under this system. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=atomicconspiracy>Atomic Conspiracy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 118<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(1/6/03 8:14:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Enough horse manure</span><hr size=1> Mexico could not invade even a nuclear blasted California or any other significant part of the US. Mexico itself would suffer catastrophic damage in a nuclear war, economic dislocation would create a similar situation to what you postulate for Africa. <br>
Beyond that, it is impossible for any foreign country to invade the United States, even after a nuclear holocaust. There are millions of people in this country who have made a hobby and avocation of nuclear survival for decades. Many of these are bat-cave fantasists but their guns, shelters, and stocks of MREs are real enough. Many others, less publicity concious, have a very solid grip on the problems and potential solutions.  There is no comparable movement in other countries. Indeed, even in this country, the Hollywood/Madison Avenue Axis regards Survivalists as mortal enemies and represents them as a band of violent psychopaths. Fine, this only means that the fifth-columnists and their media crazed supporters would be eliminated root and branch by their own choice. <br>
With or without a nuclear holocaust, there is no hope at all for subjugating the United States by force.  American citizens own more firearms than all the armies of the world combined. There are 100 American cities in which armed citizens outnumber any of the Euro-Islamic Axis armies. There are 14 in which they outnumber all the Euro-Islamic forces combined. Even if our armed forces were forced to disband (probably by a peacenik-endorsed hostage situation or some similar unheard-of atrocity), their weapons could not be seized or even reliably accounted for. They are stored everywhere in the country, and in many places outside it. <br>
There are hundreds of people in this country who know how to make such things as surface-to-air and anti-tank missiles in their garages. A few know how to make atomic bombs, and could do so if a few restrictions were removed, as they undoubtedly would be in this situation. Millions, literally millions, can make small arms ammunition, grenades and landmines. There are 100,000 small aircraft in this country, many of which could present an impossible air defense problem if properly (though easily) modified. Imagine 40,000 armed ultralights, equipped with night vision devices (millions of which are in private hands) and likely to pop up at any point on the map. <br>
There are 40 million veterans in this country. Three million of these have both seen combat and are under 65 years of age. <br>
<br>
